Package: curveRep
Type: Package
Title: Visualizing Data Through Curvilinear Representations of Matrices
Version: 1.1
Date: 2017-08-23
Author: Daniel K. Sewell
Maintainer: Daniel K. Sewell <daniel-sewell@uiowa.edu>
Description: This package visualizes any arbitrary matrix by first mapping the matrix to a set of functions. These functions can exactly represent the matrix, distances between objects, or the correlation structure in the data.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Depends: R (>= 3.2.3), splines, mclust, rARPACK, RColorBrewer, Matrix
LazyData: true
